 &UR; CABLE:  &LR; By all accounts, AT&AMP;T's efforts to sell local phone service
in California three years ago was a disaster. Thousands of
residential customers had to wait weeks to be switched over from
Pacific Bell, partly because of glitches in Pac Bell's order
system. Others lost their dial tone for several days. And AT&AMP;T said
it was forced to pay so much to Pac Bell, which controls the local
phone lines, that it had little hope of ever turning a profit.  &UR; BY
