``Forrest Gump,'' ``My Fellow Americans'' and ``Patch Adams.''
</P>
<P>
   There are several homes for estate employees that have sat on
the 8,000 acres since George Vanderbilt, Cornelius Vanderbilt's
grandson, opened the house on Christmas Eve, 1895. While George
Vanderbilt created the homes for people who helped run the farm,
they are now used for agriculture staff, security guards and other
employees whose jobs require them to be nearby.
</P>
<P>
   Q: What effect do the forest fires out West have on our smog
conditions?
</P>
<P>
   A: Nobody really knows, said Ted Russell, professor of civil and
environmental engineering at Georgia Tech. Some air particles, such
as sand and soot, can travel great distances.
</P>
<P>
   Sand from the Sahara Desert in Africa has been found in the air
