   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   NEWS-QUESTIONS _ Q&AMP;A on the news, in two takes. (Bessonette,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) (EDS: Moving on l (Lifestyle) and a
(General News) categories.) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CONSUMER NEWS
</P>
<P>
   SHOWERHEADS _ A lot of home improvement jobs are tricky and may
turn out to be more complicated than you expect. Other jobs are so
easy that one class at a home improvement store or 30 minutes
helping someone with experience will teach you all you need to
know. I've found that changing a shower head can fall into either
category. (Cummings, Dayton Daily News) WITH PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   WASHERS _ Automatic washers and dryers have taken most of the
physical labor out of getting our clothes and linens clean, but it
now takes smarts to do the laundry. A look at the new generation of
washers and dryers, plus a sidebar on energy labels. (Dayton Daily
News) WITH PHOTOS AND ILLUSTRATION
</P>
<P>
   BUYER'S-EDGE _ Totes for tots (and the people who love them).
How-to-buy and what-to-look-for guide to diaper bags for the modern
mother (and father) _ forget the cutesy baby pinks and blues. Even
handbag designer Kate Spade has come out with a version of the old
standby. And there are back-pack styles that are easy to carry.
(Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   SHOPPING-GUIDE _ A weekly feature telling how to locate
hard-to-find items. This week: (Johnson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   SHOPPING-DESTINATION _ A weekly feature about fun places to shop
in the Southeast. This week: (Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH
PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD
</P>
<P>
   COXNET FOOD _ (EDS: This is the CoxNet FOOD page for the current
week. This layout is now available.)
</P>
<P>
   COXNET FOOD 0829 -- Picking out a good cantaloupe is a risky
roll of the dice most months of the year. We lift it, because we
know it should feel heavy. We eyeball it, looking for errant traces
of green. We sniff it, hoping for sweet fragrance. We take it home.
Cut into it. And it is tasteless. In August, the odds switch to our
favor. (Heller, Dayton Daily News) Art includes a 4-column color
photo of Melon and Prosciutto and a 2-column color photo of
Cantaloupe Sorbet and a 4-column color photo of different types of
cantaloupes and a 1-column color photo of a cantaloupe for a
headline treatment.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: RECIPES -- Recipes for Melon and Prosciutto with Balsimic
Vinegar, Cantaloupe Sorbet, Melon Compote and Melon and Red Pepper
Salsa.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: CYBERSPICE -- Summer is the salad season. When heat and
humidity put a crimp on appetites, a main-dish salad is a healthful
way to get dinner on the table. (Parham, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) With recipe for Pasta Salad with Sweet
Peppers and Dill.
</P>
