<P>
   VIDEO-RINGEL _ For Labor Day, Eleanor Ringel Gillespie looks at
union movies, including ``Matewan,'' ``Hoffa'' and ``On The
Waterfront.'' Ringel, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   AUDIO-DOMINGO-VOIGT _ Pierre Ruhe reviews ``Domingo and Voigt
sing Wagner Love Duets'' CD by Placido Domingo, Deborah Voigt.
Grade A. (Ruhe, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   AUDIO-MINIS _ Mini reviews of new CDs: Eric Bibb (Don Melvin,
A-), Bill Monroe tribute (Russ, B+), Irma Thomas (Eileen, B-),
``Today Show Concerts'' (Nick, B-).(Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-NOTES _ Book publishers that once dismissed the black
audience as non-readers are now trying to cash in on a growing
market. Random House and Kensington are joining HarperCollins and
Time Warner in launching new imprints aimed at African-Americans. .
. . Patricia Cornwell has signed a $5 million movie deal for the
rights to all of her Kay Scarpetta books . . . . A survey by Teen
magazine shows troubling statistics about the reading habits of
teenage girls. (O'Briant, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HOME AND GARDEN
</P>
<P>
   GARDENING-LIFE _ A gardening column by Lee May. This week: You
say ``herb,: I say ``erb''. When it comes to consistency in
gardening, let's call the whole thing off.(May, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
