<P>
   DIAMONDS _ As the diamond industry around the world struggles to
free itself from conflict diamonds _ so that consumers can be sure
the rings on their fingers didn't pay to cut of someone else's arm
_ we look at how local diamond dealers are trying to deal with the
issue. (Searer, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   CHENEY _ GOP vice presidential nominee Dick Cheney campaigns in
Atlanta Wednesday, blasting the Clinton-Gore administration for
what he says is a poor record of support for the military. Georgia
Democrats slap back, saying Cheney is resorting to a tired
Republican line of attacking Democrats on the military to avoid
getting into the real issues -- the lack of detail by the
Bush-Cheney ticket on health insurance for children and plans for
providing prescription drug coverage for the elderly. (Pruitt,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
