over Latin America, using on-air personalities hired from those
countries. We take a look at the Weather Channel/Latin America, at
the challenges it has faced in getting people in Latin America used
to relying on forecasts, and the community of Hispanics and
Brazilians who are pioneering this effort. (Melvin, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   OPED/EDITORIAL
</P>
<P>
   MCCARTY-COLUMN _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Paralyzed since a May 15
shooting, Dayton police officer Mary Beall has been undergoing
intensive therapy since being transferred from Good Samaritan
Hospital in mid-June. The hospitalstaff had come to regard her as
family. (McCarty, Dayton Daily News) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ People who want to mingle government and
religion argue that the words ``separation of church and state'' do
not appear in the Constitution. They're right. But neither do the
words ``interstate commerce,'' ``separation of powers'' or ``right
to privacy.'' They are, however, fundamental constitutional
principles. (Nethaway, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
<P>
