<P>
   APOLOGY _ Corporate America is learning a word that's old hat to
most folks. Sorry. That's the subtext of high-profile TV
commercials from Ford Motor Co. concerning the Firestone tire
fiasco and from United Airlines about a summer-long spate of flight
delays and cancellations. The ads feature top executives.
``Clearly, the most effective way to deal with a crisis is full
disclosure, right up front,'' said Jeff Springston, an associate
professor of advertising 0and marketing at the University of
Georgia. ``The public will forgive mistakes, but they'll never
forgive a lie.'' (Leith, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   CNN _ Rick Kaplan's departure from CNN is part of a larger
