nation was a culinary prisoner, its cooking a distant imitation of
the not-so-enticing food back home. No more. As the world tunes in
to the Sydney Games in September, it will discover a city and
nation undergoing a transformation that reminds some people of the
gastronomical reawakening that began in California a generation
ago. A guide to uniquely Aussie tastes, plus recipes for classics
such as Pavlova and ``Mod-Oz'' (Modern Australian) creations
blending multicultural flavors, from some of Sydney's hottest
chefs.(Auchmutey, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH COLOR PHOTO
