<P>
   BKN-HARDAWAY _ The love of money is the root of all evil, the
scriptures say, but Tim Hardaway has his own interpretation. Love
is money, he believes, or so it is implied in the angry avalanche
of words he's pouring over reporters in Hawaii. There, in paradise
with the U.S. Olympic basketball team, the Miami Heat point guard
purports to be in purgatory. Free agency isn't supposed to be this
frustrating for a five-time All-Star like Timmy. Free agency is
supposed to be a time to savor, a time to be courted by NBA teams
with championship dreams, a time to ask for the moon, or at least
the monetary equivalent of what it took to send Neil Armstrong
there. Something changed for Hardaway, however, something he can't
see and won't acknowledge. He got hurt, repeatedly. He got old,
inevitably. And he became, consequently, more of a health risk than
a supernatural contract reward warrants. (George, Palm Beach Post)
