<SLUG> BC-COOK'S-CORNER-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SLOW AND STEADY COOKS THE DINNER
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By NATALIE HAUGHTON 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Boy, do we love our slow cooker recipes! When the call went out
for easy recipes for Sue Dietel of La Canada, several readers
shared their favorites. Many wrote that their creations are simple
and delicious. There are plenty of options to try, so pull out that
trusty pot and get cooking! &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
BBQ BEEF SANDWICHES &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Shared by A.J. Rowbottom, North Hollywood) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 medium onion, chopped &QL;
</P>
<P>
   3 cloves garlic OR 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder &QL;
</P>
<P>
   3 pounds boneless beef chuck OR bottom round roast, cut into 4
pieces &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon salt &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon pepper &QL;
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup water &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 cups barbecue sauce &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Buns OR kaiser rolls &QL;
</P>
<P>
   In a slow cooker, place onions and garlic on bottom, top with
beef chunks and sprinkle beef with salt and pepper. Add water and
cover.
</P>
<P>
   Cook on low heat setting 9 to 9 1/2 hours or until beef falls
apart with a fork. No stirring is necessary during cooking.
</P>
<P>
   Remove all liquid from beef (makes an excellent gravy for mashed
potatoes). Trim and discard excess fat from cooked beef.
</P>
<P>
   Shred beef with two forks until no solid pieces remain. Add
barbecue sauce and mix thoroughly. Serve on buns or rolls. Makes
about 7 to 8 cups of shredded barbecue beef. May be covered and
refrigerated up to 4 days. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SLOW COOKER CHICKEN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Shared by Marion Brussel, Canyon Country) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 (10 3/4-ounce) can cream of mushroom OR cream of celery soup &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 package onion soup mix &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 cups white wine &QL;
</P>
<P>
   3 or 4 chicken breasts &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Mix together soups and wine. Pour over chicken in a slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low heat setting 6 to 8 hours OR on high heat
setting 3 to 4 hours. Serve over noodles or rice. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SLOW COOKER CARNITAS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Shared by Patricia Thomas, Sun Valley) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 (3- to 4-pound) blade OR shoulder pork roast &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 cup green chili salsa &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon garlic powder &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Place meat piece whole in a slow cooker. Dump salsa over top.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
</P>
<P>
   Cover and cook on low heat setting 8 to 10 hours. Drain off fat.
Remove bone. Shred meat and return to pot to keep warm until
serving.
</P>
<P>
   Serve with warm tortillas and a squeeze of lime. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
TERIYAKI STEAK &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Shared by Julie Luce, Lancaster) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 to 2 1/2 pounds boneless chuck steak &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon ground ginger &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon sugar &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons oil &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup soy sauce &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 clove garlic, crushed &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Cut steak into 1/8-inch-thick slices. Combine remaining
ingredients in a small bowl. Place meat in a slow cooker. Pour
sauce over. Cover and cook on low heat setting 6 to 8 hours. Serve
with rice and veggies. Makes about 5 to 6 servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
KONA CHICKEN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Shared by Julie Luce, Lancaster) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   3 to 4 pounds chicken fryer parts OR 2 small broilers,
quartered &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Salt and pepper &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup chopped green onions &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup soy sauce &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup dry white wine &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup water &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup honey &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper and place in a slow
cooker. Combine green onions, soy cause, wine and water. Pour over
chicken.
</P>
<P>
   Cover and cook on low heat setting 3 to 4 hours or until chicken
is tender.
</P>
<P>
   Remove chicken from pot. Arrange on a broiler pan and brush
honey on chicken. Broil until golden brown, brushing with honey
several times. Makes 6 to 8 servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
BEEF POT ROAST &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Shared by Vivian Cooper, Encino) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 (3- to 4-pound) beef rump roast, 7-bone roast OR pot roast &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 (4-ounce) can sliced mushrooms, drained OR about 12 fresh
mushrooms, sliced &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup beef consomme OR water &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 (1 3/8-ounce) envelope dry onion soup mix &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Put meat in a slow cooker. Add mushrooms. Mix beef consomme with
dry onion soup mix. Pour over all. Cover and cook on low heat
setting 10 to 12 hours or on high heat setting 5 to 6 hours. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
CRANBERRY POT ROAST &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Shared by Gilda N. Wilcox, Woodland Hills) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 (3- to 4-pound) pork roast (boneless OR pork loin roast may be
used) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Salt and pepper &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 cup ground OR finely chopped cranberries &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup honey &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon grated orange peel &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/8 teaspoon ground cloves &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/8 teaspoon ground nutmeg &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Sprinkle roast with salt and pepper. Place in 4 1/2-quart slow
cooker. Combine all remaining ingredients and pour over roast.
Cover and cook on low heat setting 8 to 10 hours. Makes 6 to 8
servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
CRAN-ORANGE TURKEY ROLL &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Shared by Gilda N. Wilcox, Woodland Hills) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup sugar &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons cornstarch &QL;
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup orange marmalade &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 cup fresh cranberries, ground OR finely chopped &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 (2- to 2 1/2-pound) frozen turkey roll, partially thawed &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Salt and pepper &QL;
</P>
<P>
   In small saucepan, blend sugar and cornstarch; stir in marmalade
and cranberries. Cook and stir until mixture is bubbly and slightly
thickened.
</P>
<P>
   Place partially thawed turkey roll in a 4 1/2-quart slow cooker.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper. Pour sauce over turkey.
Cover and cook on low heat setting 9 to 10 hours or until done.
Check last 2 to 3 hours. Slice turkey roll; spoon sauce over. Makes
6 servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
CHICKEN LEGS WITH DRIED FRUIT &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Shared by Ruth Nebron, Valley Glen) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 large onion, sliced &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Grated peel and juice of 1 orange &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons soy sauce &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons Dijon mustard &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon minced garlic &QL;
</P>
<P>
   8 chicken thighs OR 4 thighs and 4 drumsticks, skin removed &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 cup dried fruit (1/2 cup dried apricots and 1/2 cup dried
cranberries OR other combination) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Place onions on bottom of a slow cooker.
</P>
<P>
   Mix orange peel and juice, Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce,
mustard and garlic in large bowl. Add chicken pieces and toss to
mix.
</P>
<P>
   Place chicken mixture in cooker; add dried fruit. Cover and cook
on low heat setting 6 to 8 hours or until chicken is tender. &QL; 
--- &QL; 
Can you help?
</P>
<P>
   If you have recipes that can help this reader, please send them
along to us at the address below to share in a future column.
</P>
<P>
   Q. I've lost a great Cranberry Walnut Jam recipe that I clipped
from the paper about six years ago. Help! _ JoAnn Inouye,
Chatsworth &QL; 
--- &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Cook's Corner welcomes recipe requests from readers. While we
cannot reply to them individually, we will answer those of general
interest in this column. Also, if you can help another reader with
a recipe request, write to Cook's Corner, Daily News Food
Department, P.O. Box 4200, Woodland Hills, Calif. 91365-4200.
Please be sure recipes specify exact package sizes, can and pan
sizes and baking times and temperatures.
</P>
<P>
   Recipes printed are from the source indicated and have not been
tested by the Daily News Food Department unless noted. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
