<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUYERS-EDGE31-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Diaperbags to drool for
 &HT;    By Sabine Morrow
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   With many of us lugging briefcases, cellphones, Palm Pilots,
laptops, lunch boxes and handbags, leaving the house is no
lightweight task these days.
</P>
<P>
   Add a baby and you've got your hands _ and arms _ full.
</P>
<P>
   A roomy, well-designed diaper bag could make your life a lot
easier and keep that tot well-stocked with baby must-haves when
you're both on the run.
</P>
<P>
   That old-fashioned frilly, pink-and-blue quilted diaper bag your
mother dragged around is pretty much a relic. Today's versions run
the gamut from rough and tumble nylon backpack styles equipped with
cellphone pockets to sleek and sexy satin looks brandishing tony
designer monikers and matching price tags.
</P>
<P>
   When shopping for a diaper bag, remember that while looks do
count, they aren't everything.
</P>
<P>
   What do you really need?
</P>
<P>
   Since it's going to get a major workout, purchase a durable bag
that can take some abuse. For comfort's sake, something with a
flexible shoulder strap makes sense. Also, look for a diaper bag
with features such as a full-size, fairly thick changing pad, a
removable dirty duds bag and plenty of easy-to-access nooks and
crannies. If it's machine washable, that's a bonus. But a fabric
you can wipe clean is a must.
</P>
<P>
   And let's not forget Dad. We found a slew of diaper bags in
neutral colors that easily pass for gym totes or overnight bags.
</P>
<P>
   Since many of these diaper bags will be pressed into doing
double duty as a handbag or briefcase, consider getting travel-size
baby powder, lotions and even baby wipes. They'll take up less
room, allowing space for your keys, wallet and that Palm Pilot.
</P>
<P>
   Here's a sample of the diaper bags we found that can accommodate
just about any lifestyle and budget.
</P>
<P>
   Sabine Morrow writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
