<SLUG> BC-FOOD-RECIPESWAP31-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Corn bread takes cheeses and broccoli
 &HT;    By Marcia Langhenry
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When we published a corn bread recipe recently that contained
shrimp, it prompted Pat Cornick of Peachtree City, Ga., to ask for
one she remembered that included broccoli, and cottage and cheddar
cheeses. Several readers responded, including Susan Lindley of
Atlanta. She sent this one she got about 10 years ago from the
Farmers Market Bulletin published by the Georgia Department of
Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
   ``It is not low fat, but it is wonderful,'' Lindley said.
</P>
<P>
   If you don't have an iron skillet, bake in any dark pan.
</P>
<P>
   BREAD
</P>
<P>
   Broccoli Cheese Corn Bread
</P>
<P>
   Makes 8 servings
</P>
<P>
   Preparation time: about 15 minutes
</P>
<P>
   Cooking time: 35-45 minutes
</P>
<P>
   Grease for the pan
</P>
<P>
   1 (8 1/2-ounce) box corn bread mix
</P>
<P>
   1 (10-ounce) package frozen, chopped broccoli, thawed and
drained
</P>
<P>
   1 small onion, chopped fine
</P>
<P>
   1 green onion, chopped
</P>
<P>
   1 cup grated cheddar cheese or cottage cheese, or a mixture of
both to equal 1 cup
</P>
<P>
   4 eggs, slightly beaten
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup (1 stick) butter,
</P>
<P>
   softened
</P>
<P>
   Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease an iron skillet and place in
oven to heat.
</P>
<P>
   Combine corn bread mix, broccoli, onions, cheeses, eggs and
butter. Pour into hot skillet. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes, or until
golden brown.
</P>
<P>
   Per serving: 301 calories, 12 grams protein, 19 grams fat
(percent calories from fat, 56), 22 grams carbohydrates, 139
milligrams cholesterol, 460 milligrams sodium, 4 grams fiber.
</P>
<P>
   Request
</P>
<P>
   Anne Eisenhardt e-mailed a request for Cumberland Chicken _
chicken baked with a sauce based on red currant jelly.
</P>
<P>
   Contacting this column
</P>
<P>
   Recipes or requests should be sent to Recipe Swap, Food
Department, The Atlanta Journal-Constitution, P.O. Box 4689,
Atlanta, GA 30302. Fax: 404-526-5509. Include a daytime phone
number.
</P>
<P>
   E-mail: mlanghenry(at)ajc.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
