<P>
   COXNET FOOD _ (EDS: This is the CoxNet FOOD page for the current
week. This layout is now available.)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-AUSTRALIA _ Australia used to be strictly a fish-and-chips
kind of place. From its beginnings as a British penal colony, the
nation was a culinary prisoner, its cooking a distant imitation of
the not-so-enticing food back home. No more. As the world tunes in
to the Sydney Games in September, it will discover a city and
nation undergoing a transformation that reminds some people of the
gastronomical reawakening that began in California a generation
ago. A guide to uniquely Aussie tastes, plus recipes for classics
such as Pavlova and ``Mod-Oz'' (Modern Australian) creations
blending multicultural flavors, from some of Sydney's hottest
chefs. (Auchmutey, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH COLOR PHOTO
and LAYOUT.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   GLOSSARY _ Glossary of Aussie food terms (Auchmutey, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-AUSTRALIA-RECIPES _ Recipe page to go with Australia story
centerpieced on AJC weekly food section. (Auchmutey, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH LAYOUT.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-RECIPESWAP _A weekly recipe exchange column. This week:
Broccoli cheese corn bread. (Langhenry, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
