   ENTERTAINMENT-ARTS
</P>
<P>
   CNN _ Rick Kaplan's departure from CNN is part of a larger
executive shake-up announced today by the Atlanta-based network.
Phil Kent, formerly chief of Turner Broadcasting's international
unit, assumes the newly created job of president and coo of CNN
News Group, while three other network insiders are being promoted.
The moves, which could make Kent the heir apparent to CNN Chairman
Tom Johnson, come as the network faces two big issues: sagging
ratings and a pending merger with AOL. (Kempner/Kloer, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   Also moving in financial (f) category
</P>
<P>
   WEBRADIO _ iTurf is a Web site aimed at teens. The company that
runs the site has launched a new radio component that is live
weekdays from 1 p.m.-1 a.m., with a chat function that hooks up
listeners to each other and the DJ. Listeners can discuss the music
as it plays. Along with Soundbreak.com and a couple of other sites,
this represents a growing trend in live, DJ-hosted Internet-only
radio. (Drennen, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE _ Our wrestling columnist keeps up with the
latest twists and turns of the soap opera of professional wrestling
_ in the ring and behind the scenes. (Allen, Cox News Service)
MOVED TUESDAY.
