``Today Show Concerts'' (Nick, B-) (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-NOTES _ Book publishers that once dismissed the black
audience as non-readers are now trying to cash in on a growing
market. Random House and Kensington are joining HarperCollins and
Time Warner in launching new imprints aimed at African-Americans. .
. . Patricia Cornwell has signed a $5 million movie deal for the
rights to all of her Kay Scarpetta books . . . . A survey by Teen
magazine shows troubling statistics about the reading habits of
teenage girls. (O'Briant, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
