<HEADLINE>
MORE WAYS TO WEAR STRONG COLORS 
WITH PHOTO 
BY LINDA GILLAN GRIFFIN
</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  c. 2000 Houston Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   All the color for fall is not in the fabric of clothing. Many
women will choose to update their existing wardrobes or new
neutrals with bright accessories.
</P>
<P>
   Think orange _ safety orange, road-cone orange, autumnal orange,
deep rust. One of nature's most eye-popping colors also is
predicted to be one of the most popular this fall.
</P>
<P>
   In the photo, accessories with orange spice include a beaded
Etro shawl, $930; sunglasses by Alberta Ferretti, $110; orange
suede fringed jacket by Gilles Ricart City, $335; and Oscar de la
Renta couture necklace, $880. All from Pryorities, a Houston
boutique. Plaid wool Mary Jane shoes are by Kate Spade, $235 at
Saks Fifth Avenue.
</P>
