u l BC-FASH-MAKEUP-HNS &LR;      08-30 0961
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FASH-MAKEUP-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PUTTING ON A FALL FACE 
WITH PHOTOS
</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By LINDA GILLAN GRIFFIN 
c. 2000 Houston Chronicle 
Color both seduces and scares women.
<TEXT>
<P>
   A makeup artist may suggest a color, and the color may look
good. But if a woman doesn't like it she won't wear it.
</P>
<P>
   ``You can tell a woman `This color will bring out your skin
tone, your eye color, brighten you up.' But if for some reason,
somewhere in her childhood, her mother wore a lipstick she just
hated, then she won't wear that color. It's just psychology,'' said
Heidi Schulze, a makeup artist at Michael Kemper Salon.
</P>
<P>
   But while a woman may not like orange, for example, there are a
lot of variations of a color, she said.
</P>
<P>
   Wearing of the orange
</P>
<P>
   If a woman is going to wear orange outfits, and she is a
brunette, Schulze will pull bronze or copper into her makeup for
fall.
</P>
<P>
   If she's a blonde, Schulze will add charcoal browns and coral
tones, so the woman has a little pink in her makeup. Coral, she
said, is simply another shade of orange, one mixed with pink.
</P>
<P>
   ``A redhead? That's too easy,'' Schulze said. ``She can wear any
shade of orange _ unless she's auburn. Then she needs a cooler
tone, something more tomatoey but with blue undertones.''
</P>
<P>
   In fall, blue tones usually abound, in cosmetics and clothing.
People tend to be paler. ``But they have to keep some warmness in
their look or they look ghoulish,'' Schulze said.
</P>
<P>
   Also, she said, as women get older and their hair grays, they
tend to wear more blue tones, but that can be a mistake if their
teeth have also discolored. ``They can start to look like Morticia
Addams'' of TV's ``The Addams Family.''
</P>
<P>
   Go for green
</P>
<P>
   Greens in clothing are nice colors for lots of people, Schulze
said. ``If they want a cool citrus green (eye shadow), they can mix
it with charcoal or gray browns to their makeup to produce a cooler
look. Use a khaki or eucalyptus in the crease of the eye or a green
cake liner. Or forest green mascara. You can also use black mascara
and just tip the lashes with the color mascara.''
</P>
<P>
   Wear magenta or even fuchsia
</P>
<P>
   These are very blue-based colors, said Schulze, and magenta has
more of a purple base than fuchsia.
</P>
<P>
   ``These colors look really good on a blonde, but you want a very
soft eye, an icy eye, in silver or gray or shimmery white. It is a
good idea to pretty closely match your lipstick and lip pencil to
your outfit.''
</P>
<P>
   Pretty in winter pink
</P>
<P>
   Schulze recommends that women older than 40 save bubblegum pink
clothing for spring, but if they must wear it, she recommends using
a lavender lip gloss to take off the neon edge.
</P>
<P>
   ``It is very hard for older women to wear neon-bright colors,''
she said.
</P>
<P>
   Makeup artist Laura Mercier recommends wearing a lip color more
vibrant than the pink worn during fall or winter. She suggests
blue-red tones or layering a deep blue-red with silver.
</P>
<P>
   Brown out
</P>
<P>
   With the emphasis on camel, brown, crocodile and python this
fall and winter, there is the possibility women will go too far
into brown-toned cosmetics, creating a washed-out look.
</P>
<P>
   ``You have two options,'' said Mercier, whose Temptress look for
fall includes strong red and red-brown lipcolors.
</P>
<P>
   ``You can either play up the color on your face by using smoky
eye colors with a very sexy red lip color, or you can use `happy'
browns. These have a tint of red that makes them more intense than
a regular khaki color.''
</P>
<P>
   In the Laura Mercier line, she recommends Temptation and Cognac
eye colors and Quartz or Lust lipsticks.
</P>
<P>
   Luxury woman look
</P>
<P>
   Wearing black or black-and-white fashions is one of the surest
ways to achieve this fall's luxury-woman look, but it requires
special makeup.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's the fall to look a little more glamorous,'' Schulze said.
``The black-and-white eye is good but pull in a little silver and
wear bright red lipstick. Pull in dark as eyeliner.''
</P>
<P>
   Basically black-and-white eye makeup can also benefit from
pulling in colors such as periwinkle or lavender tones, but not
blue or turquoise.
</P>
<P>
   For fall, perhaps the most important thing to remember is that
there should be only one strong thing on your face.
</P>
<P>
   ``You don't want your face to enter the room before you do,''
Schulze said. With a dramatic eye, she recommends a soft lip, maybe
a berry stain instead of lipstick. With a bright, strong, lacquered
lip, she uses a smudged, softened eye.
</P>
<P>
   On cheeks, Schulze uses a bit of color, such as a soft warm
peach or bronze, or a sheer wash of pink, such as Trish McEvoy's
new Cheeky.
</P>
<P>
   Keep the basics
</P>
<P>
   ``What I learned when I studied portrait painting as an
artist,'' said Cynthia Christ, owner of Sensia Salon, ``is that
rather than changing the foundation color, it's better to change
the powder. For example, if someone is trying to wear the orange
colors, I change them to a yellow-based powder. If they're trying
to wear some of the new plums and burgundies, I might change them
to a rosy-based powder.
</P>
<P>
   ``By changing the powder color they look more natural,'' Christ
said.
</P>
<P>
   How-to help
</P>
<P>
   If the finer points of makeup application are missing in your
education, check Mercier's makeup video, ``Laura Mercier: Flawless
Face.''
</P>
<P>
   Priced at $25, the recently released instructional video
accompanies Mercier, one of the world's most in-demand makeup
artists, as she shares some of her secrets with six real women of
various ages and racial backgrounds.
</P>
<P>
   This is a fine way to learn why Mercier, who launched her own
makeup line four years ago, is in demand by celebrities such as
Madonna, Julia Roberts, Celine Dion and Susan Sarandon.
</P>
<P>
   X X X END OF STORY
</P>
<P>
   $$$
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-30-00 1833EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
