<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Thursday, Aug. 31, and thereafter. For questions on story, contact
Stewart Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   JOB-RATINGS (Los Angeles) _ Think your job is the pits? You may
be right, according to the latest edition of ``Jobs Rated
Almanac,'' a book ranking the best and worst jobs in the country.
Topping the list is financial planner, for its plentitude of low
stress, short work weeks and high income. At the other end are
movie stars and athletes. By Dana Bartholomew. (Will move in the
``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   LA-CRIME (Los Angeles) _ Police Chief Bernard Parks says he
believes the recent crime wave will get worse as a baby boom in the
1990s turns into tomorrow's criminals. ``Crime will be off the
map,'' Parks said during a meeting with Daily News reporters and
editors. He has proposed integrating community and school
intervention programs with more patrols. By Rick Orlov. (Will move
