   INSIDE STORIES PROMOTED ON PAGE 1:
</P>
<P>
   GERMANY-NEONAZIS (Berlin) _ Three young neo-Nazis are convicted
of murder Wednesday for beating an African immigrant to death, and
one of them is sentenced to life imprisonment, the heaviest
punishment under German law. By Roger Cohen. (The story has moved
in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   U.N.-RELIGION (United Nations) _ On a gathering of religious
leaders from around the world at the United Nations. By Gustav
Niebuhr. (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   SALINGER-MEMOIR (Undated) _ A memoir by J.D. Salinger's daughter
reveals intimate details of her childhood growing up in the
household of the reclusive writer. By Dinitia Smith. (The story and
an ABRIDGED version have moved in ``e'' news file.)
</P>
