   CNN-FUTURE (Undated) _ In 1997, CNN's executives were looking
for something to make it the news outlet of record all of the time.
So they hired Richard N. Kaplan, an ABC News producer, in the hope
that as the president of their U.S. operation, he would bring to
CNN what the broadcast networks already had: highly produced news
programming so compelling that millions of people would tune in
regularly whether there is big news or not. The dual announcements
Wednesday that Kaplan was resigning and that CNN's entire executive
structure was being revamped, were accompanied by admissions that
the strategy did not work. By Jim Rutenberg.
