<SLUG> BC-HOLLYWOOD-BOWL-LADN </SLUG>
  
Tchaikovsky at the Bowl 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By VALERIE KUKLENSKI 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The hills will be alive tonight with the sounds of cannons as
the Hollywood Bowl Orchestra kicks off a three-night run of its
popular Tchaikovsky Spectacular. The San Francisco Ballet will
perform the well-known Act II of Peter Iliyich Tchaikovsky's ``Swan
Lake,'' and the orchestra will bring lush romance to the evening
with the Romeo and Juliet Fantasy-Overture.
</P>
<P>
   The USC Trojan Marching Band will help pull out the stops on the
1812 Overture, complete with roaring cannons and fireworks. It's a
rare reprise of the 1997 Tchaikovsky concert program.
</P>
<P>
   ``Three years ago when we did three performances, we sold 50,000
seats, which is phenomenal,'' said John Mauceri, principal
conductor of the Hollywood Bowl Orchestra.
</P>
<P>
   ``Under normal circumstances, I never repeat a program. This was
deemed so special and so beautiful, and since the San Francisco
Ballet was available (the company had rechoreographed the piece
just for the limited space of the Bowl), we decided to do it
again.''
</P>
<P>
   Mauceri said Tchaikovsky has proved to be the most popular
classical composer with Bowl audiences.
</P>
<P>
   ``The 1812 Overture with fireworks is one of those memories of a
Bowl performance that people carry with them,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Apparently, it's even memorable when the 1812 is NOT performed.
</P>
<P>
   ``Last summer, a visiting orchestra had to do Tchaikovsky
without it and there was practically a riot.''
</P>
<P>
   All right, so nobody actually flung a Williams-Sonoma picnic
hamper full of soft French cheeses on stage in protest, but the
Hollywood Bowl did get a lot of letters.
</P>
<P>
   Tickets range in price from $3 to $85 and are available at the
Bowl box office, at all Ticketmaster outlets and by credit card
phone order at (213) 480-3232. Tickets also may be purchased online
at www.hollywoodbowl.org. For additional information, call (323)
850-2050. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
