Researchers at Brandeis University have created a robotic system
that designs and builds other robots, largely without the help from
people. In the short run, this could create a new industry of
inexpensive robots customized for specific tasks. In the long run,
this is a first step along the way to robots that can reproduce and
evolve, building improved versions of themselves. ``Arrow'', one of
the robots from the Brandeis project. (Brandeis University/The New
