BC-TV-GOODY-AZR(a) 
 &HT;    REALLY, WHAT ISLAND HAVE YOU BEEN ON?(a) 
 &HT;    (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)(a) 
 &HT;    By BILL GOODYKOONTZ(a) 
 &HT;    c.2000 The Arizona Republic(a) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   (UNDATED) - One last (beginitalic)Survivor(enditalic)
observation, if you'll permit it.
</P>
<P>
   I've heard from a lot of people since Rich walked off naked,
(less) fat and happy with $1million, either by phone, e-mail or the
radio and online talk shows I've sat in on. And the astonishing
thing is this:
</P>
<P>
   Almost no one admits to watching the show.
</P>
<P>
   Now come on. Nearly 52 million people tuned in for the two-hour
finale. What gives?
</P>
<P>
   At first, this perplexed me, but then I remembered a
conversation with my predecessor in this job. Should I worry, I
asked shortly after taking over, that whenever I tell people I'm a
TV critic, they stick their nose in the air and huff, ``I don't
watch TV?''
</P>
<P>
   ``No,'' he said. And why not?
</P>
<P>
   ``They're lying.''
</P>
<P>
   I suspect something similar here. (beginitalic)You're(enditalic)
not lying, of course. All those other people are. And to them I
say: You have nothing to be ashamed of. Don't fear reality TV.
Respect it. Admitting that you watch is the first step toward a
cure.
</P>
<P>
   Now don't you feel better?
</P>
<P>
   OK, I lied. That wasn't the last (beginitalic)Survivor
(enditalic)bit. Just so you can feel secure in knowing that the
castaways are working hard to extend their window of fame, know
that Rich is going to be a presenter at the MTV Video Music Awards
next Thursday. Rich, Sue, Gervase and Jenna will appear on special
editions of (beginitalic)Hollywood Squares(enditalic). And don't
feel bad for Kelly. She hosted (beginitalic)Talk Soup (enditalic)on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
   If you're a (beginitalic)West Wing (enditalic)fan, you've got to
like reading the Emmy tea leaves. The oft-nominated NBC rookie show
won four technical awards at the Creative Arts Emmys, held
Saturday. Other notable winners: Bruce Willis for Best Guest Actor
in a comedy for his role in (beginitalic)Friends(enditalic), Jean
Smart for Best Guest Actress for her (beginitalic)Frasier
(enditalic)stint; and in drama, James Whitmore for Best Guest Actor
and Beah Richards for Best Guest Actress, both for (beginitalic)The
Practice(enditalic).
</P>
<P>
   But nothing makes me happier than this: (beginitalic)Freaks and
Geeks (enditalic)won for outstanding casting for a comedy. Sure,
it's as obscure an award as you can get. But the late great show
left high and dry by NBC deserves all the good things it gets.
</P>
<P>
   The big Emmys will be given out Sept. 10.
</P>
<P>
   $$$
